column5: Not to much of a report here, ask questions if you want, I'll be back on later.  P.S. It's Lake X
Rainbows and spec's both? Very nice Steve, well done! (looks alot like one of the stocked lakes I fish off hwy.35 in Haliburton)
A bit north of haliburton, but good guess
we have one of those lake x in quebec too with specks and bows...awesome pics
Very Pretty looking fish .. thanks for sharing !  Was this lake X accessible on foot .. or did you need a sled to get there ?
it was accessable by foot, but i sure wish i brought a sled
sweet ..specks are so beautiful. Looks like Haliburton area to me!
Nice fish ya got there, thanks for posting the pics and report
The county of Haliburton, not the village. To be really specific, slightly S/E of Dorset  .
Man oh man, I wish I was up there right now!!  Trapped under several snowbanks at the moment definitely hampers the idea of getting out for some specks!!
Nice trout guys !!!!..specially that rainbow...yummy    cheers
Fantastic Report!  That's a good day by anyones standards.
besides the rainbows are those not splake? just wondering because of the forked tail...  Hawk
The tail was not forked, it is just bent.  Specks 100%
